  "text": "In a large perspective study linked to the Danish National Patient Registry, 57,053 individuals completed a detailed self-administered food frequency questionnaire. The average time of cohort follow-up was 5.3 years. During follow-up, 69 subjects developed incident RA. Each increase in intake of 30 g fat fish (> or = 8 g fat/ 100 g fish) per day was associated with 49% reduction in the risk of RA [CITATION_1] .",
